%N A396973 Square array A(n,k), n >= 1, k >= 0, read by antidiagonals downwards, where column k is the expansion of e.g.f. B^k(x), where B(x) is the e.g.f. of A395269.
%H A396973 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="/A396973/b396973.txt">Antidiagonals n = 1..140, flattened</a>
%F A396973 E.g.f. B(x) satisfies B'(x) = 1 + B^l(x), where B^l(x) denotes the l-th iterate of B, with B(0) = 0.
%F A396973 Let a(n,k,l) = n! * [x^n] B^k(x), where B^k(x) is the k-th iterate of B.
%F A396973 a(n,0,l) = 0^(n-1) and a(n,k,l) = a(n,k-1,l) + Sum_{j=1..n-1} binomial(n-1,j) * a(j,k+l-1,l) * a(n-j,k-1,l) for k > 0.
%F A396973 A(n,k) = a(n,k,5).
%e A396973 Square array begins:
%e A396973   1,     1,     1,      1,      1,      1,       1, ...
%e A396973   0,     1,     2,      3,      4,      5,       6, ...
